physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Echocardiogram showed no structural abnormalities. Postmortem examination revealed a structurally normal heart without hypertrophy, evidence of meconium aspiration on examination of the lungs, early ischemic changes in the stomach, renal tubular vacuolization, and microsteatosis of the liver. Examination of the placenta showed rare pigmented macrophages concerning for meconium present in utero.
